    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.31.32" />
                <fw type="curatorial">32</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                <hi rend="caps">UNIVERSITY OF MISSOURI</hi>
                    <lb/>
                <hi rend="caps">COLUMBIA</hi>
                    <lb/>
                
                
                
                <hi rend="caps">COLLEGE OF ARTS AND SCIENCE</hi>
                    <lb/>
                <hi rend="caps">DEPARTMENT OF ENGLISH</hi>
                </fw>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                209 <hi rend="underline">Jesse</hi> Hall
                
                
                3-9-'61</dateline>
                
                
                
                <salute>Dear Mari Sandoz:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I've recently received the Brand Book of the <hi rend="caps">N. Y.</hi> Westerners and it reminds me that I did not thank you for that generous letter of yours regarding my <hi rend="underline">talk</hi> at the annual dinner. I thank you now, dear lady. It meant much to me.</p>
                
                <p>Did you note what was said of me in The Hitching Post? Who is "South Pass Pete"? He (or she?) does write well.</p>
                
                <p>I've been surprised to note that no mention has been made of the annual dinner and my talk. It seems a bit odd. Certainly the crowd was with me, if I know crowds; and I've known hundreds upon hundreds of them.</p>
               
                <p>Anyway I greatly appreciate your kindess, and I hope I may have the privilege of meeting you again before too long.</p>
               <closer>
               <salute>Sincerely,</salute> <signed>John Neihardt</signed>
               </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
